Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant shall complete a psychosexual evaluation and comply with all treatment recommendations.
Defendant shall not use the Internet without prior approval by agent.
Defendant may apply for expungement upon successful completion of probation.

Defendant shall undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.  Defendant does not have to comply with the sex offender registry.   Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. 
If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.

records.addlTxt: Judge Madden appeared by video.  Defendant Timothy J. Miller in court with attorney Damon Paul Stichert.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Tlusty placed agreement on the record and amends Ct. 1 to Possess Recording of Nudity without consent Wis. Stat. 942.09(2)(am)3.  Amended information filed.  DE enters a plea of no contest to the amended charge.  Plea colloquy. Court finds plea given freely, voluntarily and intelligently; accepts plea and finds DE guilty.  Court orders a withheld sentence and places DE on probation for 1 year with the following conditions: court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; complete psychosexual evaluation & comply with all treatment recommendations; no use of Internet without prior approval by agent; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.  Court orders DE is eligible for expungement if he successfully completes probation. Court orders DE not be placed on the sex offender reporting requirements. ba
